1 States Olympic Trials, USATF National Championships, NCAA National Championships,
2 high school state championships, and international competitions; and
3 WHEREAS, beyond her officiating achievements, she has a heart for and a deep
4 commitment to community service, volunteering with organizations such as Lafayette Parks
5 and Recreation, Louisiana Special Olympics, and multiple Louisiana collegiate track and
6 field officials associations; and
7 WHEREAS, her excellence has been recognized through numerous awards, including
8 the USATF Officials Service Award and the USATF President's Award; and
9 WHEREAS, Delores Murray's officiating career reflects the highest ideals of
10 sportsmanship, leadership, and service, and her contributions have left a lasting legacy on
11 the sport of track and field in Louisiana and beyond.
12 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
13 does hereby commend and congratulate Delores Murray on her induction into the USATF
14 National Officials Hall of Fame.
15 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to
16 Delores Murray.
